T FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.canadiancommentary.com/jasonr/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Quest Forum</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Okay, I wanted to explain how I will be working the quest forum.<br>
<br>
Instead of having a quest link on the web page for guild members, I will be updating the Quest forum, placing each quest under the appropriate class.  I will also create a thread for general quests that don't require any specific type of class.<br>
<br>
Why do I have the classes (Warnin asked so here is a indepth answer) basically for organization purposes.  For instance, Warnin came out with a quest for a hammer that only a certain few classes can use.  I initially accepted the quest, but passed it up since I would only be selling the item later.  If this was a quest created after our guild was started, I would post under each class that the quest was relevent for.<br>
<br>
Now, as for organization, I am planning the following.  I will be the only one creating the forum threads in the quest forum.  Clan members, if they create a quest, can go to the relevent threads and post in there.  If someone undertakes a quest, they enter the relevent class forum, select the quest they want to do, which is part of the thread, and if they have any questions they can use the general quest thread to get answers and assistance.<br>
<br>
This way we can keep track of all the quests we do, and that people are undertaking.  They will also be able to have threads devoted to that specific quest so they may post any questions there if they need some guidance.<br>
<br>
The problem with a web-site quest page is that it must be updated frequently, and there is really no way for people to ask specific questions without either posting over and over again in the general forum.<br>
<br>
With the MSG board, though, it is just a matter of posting once, and asking questions as they come in the relevent threads.<br>
<br>
I hope I made sense here, if not ask any questions and I will elaborate more.<br>
<br>
I made some changes again in the Quest Forum, check them out after you read this.  It will help you see what I mean.<br>
<br>
Raloth</font><P><img src=http://www.canadiancommentary.com/jasonr/yinyang2.jpg><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uraloth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raloth</A> at: 1/31/01 6:45:04 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#fbe5b4><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Administrator</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>102</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8B4513>2/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8B4513>6:39:26 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Quest Forum</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I still think it is more of a hassle then it is worth, buddy.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
